The management of Al-Taawoun have announced that the club will provide 5,000 free tickets to their fans for the 2022 AFC Champions League group stage match against Sepahan of Iran on Monday night. The tickets will be distributed at Gate 1 (for families) and Gate 3 (for individuals) of the King Abdullah Sports City Stadium, the club revealed through their official Twitter account. Al-Taawoun currently lead Group D with six points from their three fixtures. The Saudi team kicked off their campaign by beating Al-Duhail of Qatar 2-1, before going on to lose their next match 1-0 to Pakhtakor of Uzbekistan and recovering to beat Sepahan 3-0 in the first of their clashes.